For prime powers \( p^k \), derive \( f(p^k) \). 4. **Deriving \( f \) for Prime Powers:** For \( n = p^k \), \[ \sum_{i=0}^{k} f(p^i) = \frac{1}{p^k} \] Through analysis, find \( f(p^k) = 1 - p \). 5. **Calculating \( f(2023) \):** - \( f(7) = 1 - 7 = -6 \) - \( f(17^2) = 1 - 17 = -16 \) - Since \( f \) is multiplicative: \[ f(2023) = f(7) \times f(17^2) = (-6) \times (-16) = 96 \] **Final Answer:** \[ \boxed{96} \]
